You could use a `WebFilter` to transform the incoming request, adding your default `Content-Type` if the `Content-Type` header is missing on it

In this example, I am defaulting to `application/json`
```java
@Component
public class DefaultContentTypeWebFilter implements WebFilter {
    @Override
    public Mono&lt;Void&gt; filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {
        ServerHttpRequest request = exchange.getRequest();
        if (request.getHeaders().getContentType() == null) {
            exchange = exchange.mutate()
                    .request(request
                            .mutate()
                            .header(HttpHeaders.CONTENT_TYPE, MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_VALUE)
                            .build())
                    .build();
        }

        return chain.filter(exchange);
    }
}
```

